(27, '<p>Silver Chinoiserie Rococo Tea Caddy</p>\r\r\n', '1299477600', '0000-00-00', '1846', '9.5', '15', '7', '12.63', '1500', 0, 'Yes', '7', '<p>Chased in relief with Chinese tea-pickers, pagodas amidst C scrolls, Shells, Lion masks and flowers, cover with flower finial. This is a fine example of English Rococo style. was considered to be a French style and the heyday of the Rococo movemen', '<p>HLJ checked London hallmark--1846.</p>\r\r\n', '450', 'GBP', 'GBP', 'Shelf 15', 'B', '<p>Christie&#39;s Interiors Masters &amp; Makers Catalogue, Sale 5068, London, 8 March 2011, lot 67.</p>\r\r\n', '<p>Lot Description A VICTORIAN SILVER CHINOISERIE TEA CADDY MARK OF JOSEPH ANGELL, LONDON, 1853 Chased in relief with Chinese tea-pickers, pagodas, &quot;C&quot; scrolls, shells, lion masks and engraved panels of stylised leaves, the similarly-decora', 'Active', '', '0', '', '', '', '', 'Yes'),
