(29, '<p>Octagonal Ivory and Mother of Pearl Tea Caddy</p>\r\r\n', '1301288400', '0000-00-00', ' 1820', '10', '10', '7', '6.38', '900', 0, 'Yes', '9', '<p>The hinged lid and front decorated with stylised plant forms, centred by a silver cartouche that is unadorned. The area around the cartouche is decorated with Scrimshaw scroll work, a carving practice originally practiced by whalers and sailors be', '<p>Bibliography: Lyon &amp; Turnbull Fine Antiques Catalogue, Sale 310, London, 30 March 2011, lot 132.</p>\r\r\n', '270', 'GBP', 'GBP', 'Shelf 2', 'B', '', '<p>REGENCY IVORY AND MOTHER OF PEARL OCTAGONAL TEA CADDY CIRCA 1820 the hinged lid and front decorated with stylised plant forms, centred by a silver shield shaped cartouche 10cm wide, 10cm high, 7cm deep</p>\r\r\n', 'Active', '', '0', '', '', '', '', 'Yes'),
(36, '<p>Tortoiseshell Tea Caddy</p>\r\r\n', '1301288400', '0000-00-00', 'mid 19th century', '13', '16', '9', '0', '550', 0, 'No', '10', '<p>Sarcophagus form, the cover centred by a silver mount monogrammed &#39;EL,&#39; opening to an interior with twin lidded wells, on later bun feet. Tortoiseshell is made of two proteins keratin and chitin. This means that using heat the shell can be', '', '165', 'GBP', 'GBP', 'Shelf 2', 'C', '', '<p>VICTORIAN TORTOISESHELL TEA CADDY MID 19TH CENTURY sarcophagus form, the cover centred by a silver mount monogrammed &#39;EL&#39;, opening to an interior with twin lidded wells, on later bun feet 16cm wide, 13cm high, 9cm deep</p>\r\r\n', 'Active', '', '0', '', '', '', '', 'Yes'),
(37, '<p>Red Stoneware Teapot with George III Silver Mounts</p>\r\r\n', '1303016400', '0000-00-00', 'mounts 1790', '24', '15.2', '12', '26.78', '1600', 0, 'Yes', '11', '<p>A traditional Yixing teapot produced in the western style using the distinctive red clay for which the Yixing region is famous. The silver spout and the pineapple finial are later additions, which date to 1790. The hallmark on the lid may correspo', '<p>Later English silver mounts. With a star above, perhaps Grimwade No.3497, the mounts 1790 with faceted spout and pineapple finial.</p>\r\r\n', '480', 'GBP', 'GBP', 'Shelf 2', 'B', '', '<p>A RED STONEWARE TEAPOT WITH GEORGE III SILVER MOUNTS MAKER&#39;S MARK INDISTINCT C.? WITH A STAR ABOVE, PERHAPS GRIMWADE NO.3497, THE MOUNTS CIRCA 1790 With faceted spout and pineapple finial 6 in. (15.2 cm.) high Weighable silver 4 oz. (124 gr.)<', 'Active', '', '0', '', '', '', '', 'Yes'),
