(39, '<p>Staffordshire Tea Set</p>\r\r\n', '1303016400', '0000-00-00', '1895', '28', '13', '0', '0', '750', 0, 'No', '13', '<p>The distinctive yellow of this English porcelain tea set is stunningly set off by the fine silver detail work produced by William Comyns and sons Ltd. The firm was known for incorporating a variety of other materials into their silver work and are', '<p>This important firm of manufacturing silversmiths was established by William Comyns c. 1859 when he purchased the business of Robert Tagg, which was founded about 1730. As yet efforts to trace the latter&#39;s lineage have failed; it seems clear, ', '0', 'GBP', 'GBP', 'Shelf 15', 'A', '', '<p>Teapot, sugar bowl, milk jug, Staffordshire, William Comyns &amp; Sons ltd., London 1895.</p>\r\r\n', 'Active', '', '0', '', '', '', '', 'Yes'),
(40, '<p>Silver Tea Set by James Dixon and Sons</p>\r\r\n', '1300856400', '0000-00-00', 'composit set, 1902 and 1901', '11.4', '7.2', '9.7', '0', '900', 0, 'Yes', '14', '<p>The teapot is mirrored on the top half with fluting on the bottom half. Inspired by Queen Anne-style silver, this Victorian tea set is embossed with floral designs running up the spout and a fluted finial matching the fluting on the bottom half of', '<p>J Dixon &amp; Sons (James Dixon &amp; Sons) founded 1806 in Sheffield, was one of the major British manufacturers in the Industrial Revolution of the 19th century. They were the best-known manufacturer of Britannia metal, and also the world leader', '0', 'GBP', 'GBP', 'Shelf 9', 'C', '', '<p>1900/1 1 x 3 piece tea set, Sheffield.</p>\r\r\n', 'Active', '', '0', '', '', '', '', 'Yes'),
