(42, '<p>Traditional Victorian Silver Tea Set</p>\r\r\n', '1302152400', '0000-00-00', '1899(teapot & milk jug) 1901(sugar bowl)', '12', '9.5', '9.5', '0', '2250', 0, 'No', '16', '<p>A traditional Victorian tea set with long Balustrades rising from the base to half way up the teapot. A dark English wooden Handle and finial complement the silver of the teapot. The milk jug is part of the original set along with the Teapot but a', '<p>Teapot &amp; Milk Jug both 1899 inscribed A. C. M &amp; Co (Alexander Clark Manufacturing Co.) Sugar Bowl 1901 inscribed W M &amp; S (William Mammatt &amp; Son).</p>\r\r\n', '0', 'GBP', 'GBP', 'Shelf 17', 'C', '', '<p>Victorian sterling silver teawares; comprising teapot, sugar bowl, and cream jug in original box.</p>\r\r\n', 'Active', '', '0', '', '', '', '', 'No'),
