(58, '<p>Silver Gilt Teapot on a Stand</p>\r\r\n', '1305694800', '0000-00-00', '1785', '17', '14.5', '0', '23', '27000', 0, 'No', '32', '<p>The goldsmith Andrew Fogelbert, also identified as Anders Fogelberg, was born in Sweden in 1732 and apprenticed to a goldsmith in Halmsted in 1746. He is thought to have come to England from Sweden around 1770 and was known for silversmithing that', '<p>Silver gilt, with chased and cast decoration. Makers Mark of Andrew Fogelberg and Stephen Gilbert (Partnership from 1780-1793). The ingenious use of a stand on square tapering legs applied with swags, from which one can fit the teapot is reminisce', '0', 'GBP', 'GBP', 'Shelf 12', 'A', '', '<p>Silver gilt, London 1785, Maker&#39;s mark of Andrew Fogelbert &amp; Stephen Gilbert The ingenious use of a stand on square tapering legs applied with swags, from which one can fit the teapot is reminiscent of the decorative sketches of Sir Willia', 'Active', '', '0', '', '', '', '', 'Yes'),
