(117, '<p>Egyptian Revival Tea and Coffee Set</p>\r\r\n', '1320991200', '0000-00-00', '1810', '0', '35', '0', '120', '35000', 0, 'No', '74', '<p>Comprising a teapot, creamer, open sugar bowl and coffee jug on lampstand, this tea set is decorated with geometric borders, classical heads on the handles, and the tripod stand formed by three winged Egyptian style figures. All pieces are engrave', '<p>Christie&#39;s New York, October 18, 1994, Lot 353.</p>\r\r\n', '0', 'GBP', 'GBP', 'Shelf 3', 'A', '<p>Comprising a teapot, creamer, open sugar bowl and coffee jug on lampstand, with geometric borders, classical heads on the handles, the tripod stand formed by three winged Egyptian style figures, all piece engraved with the arms of Earl Howe. The d', '<p>Silver-gilt, London 1810, Maker&#39;s mark of Benjamin and James Smith; the design attributed to Jean-Jacques Boileau Comprising a teapot, creamer, open sugar bowl and coffee jug on lampstand, with geometric borders, classical heads on the handles', 'Active', '', '0', '', '', '', '', 'Yes'),
(118, '<p>Silver Gilt Tea Kettle and Stand</p>\r\r\n', '1320991200', '0000-00-00', '1828', '33', '44', '0', '111', '12500', 0, 'Yes', '75', '<p>Chased overall with foliage and flowers on a matted ground, this kettle is cast with the coat-of-arms of Keppel with a cadency mark for the third son impailing Clements, for Rev. Hon. Edward Southwell Keppel (1800-83).</p>\r\r\n', '<p>The arms are those of Keppel with a cadency mark for the third son impailing Clements, for Rev. Hon. Edward Southwell Keppel (1800-83), third surviving son of William, 4th Earl of Abermarle and the Hon. Elizabeth Southwell, and his wife Lady Maria', '0', 'GBP', 'GBP', 'Shelf 2', 'B', '', '<p>Chased overall with foliage and flowers on a matted ground, cast with a coat-of-arms, with overhead-swing handle, the conforming stand with central lam, marked under kettle, inside cover, on stand and lamp, the kettle further stamped &#39;STORR AN', 'Active', '', '0', '', '', '', '', 'Yes'),
