(138, '<p>Satsuma Round Box</p>\r\r\n', '1322460000', '0000-00-00', 'C 1880', '0', '0', '0', '0', '7000', 0, 'No', '95', '<p>This Satsuma box is painted with figures walking in a continuous landscape and the knop is in the form of a thistle.</p>\r\r\n', '<p>The strong demand for Satsuma wares caused other Japanese potters, particularly those of Kyoto, to produce &quot;Satsuma&quot; earthenware vessels. The Satsuma producers in Kyoto were largely located in the suburb of Awata ç²Ÿç”°. These producers ', '0', 'GBP', 'GBP', 'Shelf 9', 'A', '', '<p>Japanese Satsuma round box and cover painted with figures walking in a continuous landscape, the knop in a thistle form (small chips restored), signed Seikozan, Meiji period, c 1880.</p>\r\r\n', 'Active', '', '0', '', '', '', '', 'Yes'),
(139, '<p>Kutani Tea Caddy</p>\r\r\n', '1322805600', '0000-00-00', '1890', '0', '0', '0', '0', '150', 0, 'No', '96', '<p>An unusually shaped caddy. The gold and red enamel work highlights the rich design. The design is elegant with nods to the Ko-Kutani style around the base. The central floral design is elaborate and of the intricate style of later works. The caddy', '', '0', 'GBP', 'GBP', 'Shelf 8', 'B', '', '<p>Kutani tea caddy 1890.</p>\r\r\n', 'Active', '', '0', '', '', '', '', 'Yes'),
