(325, '<p>Walnut Novelty Tea Caddy in the Form of a Stack of Books</p>\r\r\n', '1348981200', '0000-00-00', 'Late 18th century', '0', '22.5', '0', '0', '2800', 0, 'No', '339', '<p>With pale-wood veneered leaves and punched walnut veneers simulating the spines on an oak carcase, a sliding top section revealing the key-hole and designed in the form of a stack of books.</p>\r\r\n', '', '840', 'GBP', 'GBP', 'Shelf 9', 'B', '<p>For similar see Sotheby&#39;s, The Robert Harman Collection, 12 November 1999, lot 30.</p>\r\r\n', '<p>Walnut Novelty Tea Caddy in the Form of a Stack of Books England Late 18th century George III</p>\r\r\n', 'Active', '', '0', '', '', '', '', 'Yes'),
