(454, '<p>German Silver Trembleuse</p>\r\r\n', '1354514400', '0000-00-00', '1751-1753', '0', '14', '0', '116.5', '2400', 0, 'No', '401', '<p>Detachable stand in the form of a leaf, together with a Meissen cup painted with military scenes after Rugendas. From Augsburg.</p>\r\r\n', '<p>Exh. Cat. Couven-Museum Aachen, 2003, no. 139, bought from H. Matzke, Munich by Dr. Heller</p>\r\r\n', '720', 'GBP', 'GBP', 'Shelf 5', 'B', '', '<p>A GERMAN SILVER TREMBLEUSE, JOHANN JAKOB ADAM, AUGSBURG, 1751-1753, TOGETHER WITH A MEISSEN CUP</p>\r\r\n', 'Active', '', '0', '', '', '', '', 'Yes'),
(455, '<p>Esaias Busch III Silver-Gilt Teapot</p>\r\r\n', '1354514400', '0000-00-00', '1729-1733', '0', '6.7', '0', '0', '1900', 0, 'No', '402', '<p>This miniature teapot is flat-chased, with a detachable cover, and a carved wood handle.</p>\r\r\n', '<p>Esaias Busch III, the son of Jeremiah Busch, was born in Augsburg in 1676. He became a master goldsmith in 1704 and married Catharina Barbara, the daughter of goldsmith Carl Schuch, the same year. He died in 1759.</p>\r\r\n', '570', 'GBP', 'GBP', 'Shelf 3', 'A', '<p>Exhibition Cat. Museum f&uuml;r Angewandte Kunst Frankfurt, 2011, no. 97B</p>\r\r\n', '<p>ESAIAS BUSCH III GERMAN SILVER-GILT TEAPOT, flat-chased, detachable cover, carved wood handle 6.7cm high, 2 5/8in high 116.9gr, 3oz 15 dwt, all in Augsburg, 1729-1733</p>\r\r\n', 'Active', '', '0', '', '', '', '', 'No'),
(456, '<p>Augsburg Silver Teapot and Stand</p>\r\r\n', '1354514400', '0000-00-00', '1719-1723', '0', '20.6', '0', '20', '3200', 0, 'No', '403', '<p>This Augsburg teapot has a wood handle and finial, with a gilt interior.</p>\r\r\n', '<p>Johann Wagenknecht was born around 1677. He became a master goldsmith in 1716, married the same year, and died in 1752. Esaias Busch III was born in 1676. He became a master goldsmith in 1704 and married Catharina Barbara, the daughter of goldsmit', '960', 'GBP', 'GBP', 'Shelf 9', 'AAA', '<p>Exh. Cat. Couven-Museum Aachen, 2003, no. 85 A &amp; B Klaus Pechstein, &lsquo;Sch&auml;tze deutscher Goldschmiedekunst, Erg&auml;nzung zu den Ausstellungen in L&uuml;neburg und Pforzheim&rsquo;, Weltkunst, July 1993, pp.1657-1659, fig. 417</p>\r\r\n', '<p>JOHANN WAGENKNECHT AND ESAIAS BUSCH III GERMAN SILVER TEA POT, STAND AND BURNER the teapot with wood handle and finial, gilt interior 20.6 cm, 81/4in high overall 647gr, 20oz 17dwt all in Augsburg, 1719-1723 and circa</p>\r\r\n', 'Active', '', '0', '', '', '', '', 'Yes'),
(457, '<p>Polish Parcel-Gilt Silver Canister</p>\r\r\n', '1354514400', '0000-00-00', '1665-1670', '0', '14.7', '0', '6', '6500', 0, 'No', '404', '<p>This early canister has a screw-on cover, hinged handle, and gilt interior. The underside is engraved with the initials PMK.</p>\r\r\n', '<p>Nathanael Pre&szlig;ding I, son of Danzigers Johannes Pre&szlig;ding, became a citizen of Gdansk (Danzig) in 1656 and a master goldsmith two years later. He died in 1670. His son, also Nathanael, also became a master goldsmith and was appointed Me', '1950', 'GBP', 'GBP', 'Shelf 3', 'AAA', '<p>Exh. Cat. Couven-Museum Aachen, 2003, no. 36</p>\r\r\n', '<p>NATHANAEL PRESSDING I POLISH PARCEL-GILT SILVER CANISTER AND COVER screw-on cover, hinged handle, underside with engraved initials PMK, gilt interior 14.7cm, 5 7/8 in overall height 197gr, 6oz 6dwt Gdansk (Danzig), circa 1660</p>\r\r\n', 'Active', '', '0', '', '', '', '', 'Yes'),
(458, '<p>Early Dutch Silver Gilt Teapot</p>\r\r\n', '1354514400', '0000-00-00', '1701', '0', '7.7', '0', '5', '32000', 0, 'No', '405', '<p>This Dutch teapot is an extremely early example of what later became the teapot&#39;s ubiquitous form. The pot was made by Adam Loofs, the court goldsmith of William III, King of England and Stadholder of the United Provinces of the Netherlands. W', '<p>Previously sold Sothebys London, 11 February 1985, lot 122 where the initial was incorrectly recorded as that of Augustus, Duke of Cambridge Van Ravenstein, Haarlem Engraved with a contemporary English cartouche enclosing a later royal cypher, pro', '9180', 'GBP', 'GBP', 'Shelf 3', 'AAA', '<p>Exhibited William &amp; Mary, A Crown on a Special Bond, loan exhibition on the occasion of William and Mary Tercentenary Commemoration, Sothebys Amsterdam, 12-22 November 1988, p. 57 no. 144 Literature Exh. Cat. Couven-Museum Aachen, 2003, no. 70', '<p>ADAM LOOFS A DUTCH SILVER-GILT SMALL TEAPOT, engraved with a contemporary English cartouche enclosing a later royal cypher, probably of Adolphus, Duke of Cambridge 7.7cm, 3in high 169gr, 5oz, all in The Hague, 1701,</p>\r\r\n', 'Active', '', '0', '', '', '', '', 'Yes'),
(459, '<p>Parcel Gilt Silver Canister</p>\r\r\n', '1354514400', '0000-00-00', 'C 1670', '0', '17', '0', '12', '5500', 0, 'No', '406', '<p>This early canister has eight lobes in silver- and parcel-gilt, a screw off cover, and a hinged finial. The underside is engraved for Johan Godfrid Gregori.</p>\r\r\n', '<p>Hamburg</p>\r\r\n', '1650', 'GBP', 'GBP', 'Shelf 3', 'AAA', '<p>Exh. Cat. Couven-Museum Aachen, 2003, no. 43</p>\r\r\n', '<p>ADOLF STEINWECH (STEINWEG) GERMAN PARCEL-GILT SILVER CANISTER the eight lobes silver-gilt and parcel-gilt, screw off cover and hinged finial, underside engraved Johan. Godfrid. Gregori 17cm, 6 3/4 in high 382gr, 12oz 4dwt Hamburg, circa 1670</p>\r\r', 'Active', '', '0', '', '', '', '', 'Yes'),
(460, '<p>German Silver Teapot</p>\r\r\n', '1354514400', '0000-00-00', 'C 1705', '0', '12.5', '0', '8', '1500', 0, 'No', '407', '<p>This teapot of traditional German form has a fluted body, and a crested, hinged covered spout. The pot was made by Paul Jobst S&uuml;ry who came from a well known silversmith family in Hildesheim.</p>\r\r\n', '<p>Paul Jobst S&uuml;ry, whose year of birth is unknown, came from an established family of goldsmiths from Hildesheim. He trained in the workshop of Johann Otto Graffe from 1684 to 1688, but he became a master goldsmith only in 1696. Four years late', '450', 'GBP', 'GBP', 'Shelf 9', 'A', '<p>Exh. Cat. Museum f&uuml;r Angewandte Kunst Frankfurt, 2011, no. 70B</p>\r\r\n', '<p>PAUL JOBST S&Uuml;RY (SYRING) A GERMAN SILVER TEAPOT fluted body crested, hinged covered spout 12.5cm, 4 7/8 in high 260gr, 8oz, all in Hildesheim, circa 1705</p>\r\r\n', 'Active', '', '0', '', '', '', '', 'Yes'),
(461, '<p>German Silver Teapot</p>\r\r\n', '1354514400', '0000-00-00', '1739-1749', '0', '10.6', '0', '9', '1400', 0, 'No', '408', '<p>Detachable cover, underside initialled C.C.V.H and with scratchweight W 20 1/2 L wood handle, later engraved AM in monogram below coronet, gilt interior. Made in L&uuml;beck.</p>\r\r\n', '<p>Hans Joachim Fl&ouml;th was born around 1666. He became a master goldsmith and a citizen in 1700. He was head of the local guild of goldsmiths in 1738. He retired in 1749 and was buried on 5 August 1751.</p>\r\r\n', '420', 'GBP', 'GBP', 'Shelf 5', 'B', '<p>Exh. Cat. Museum f&uuml;r Angewandte Kunst Frankfurt, 2011, no. 123A</p>\r\r\n', '<p>HANS JOACHIM FL&Ouml;TH GERMAN SILVER TEAPOT detachable cover, underside initialled C.C.V.H and with scratchweight W 20 1/2 L wood handle, later engraved AM in monogram below coronet, gilt interior 10.6cm, 4 &frac14; in high 306gr, 9oz 16dwt, all ', 'Active', '', '0', '', '', '', '', 'No'),
(462, '<p>Gold-Mounted Chinese Porcelain Teapot</p>\r\r\n', '1354514400', '0000-00-00', 'C 1720', '0', '10', '0', '0', '6500', 0, 'No', '409', '<p>The spout of this teapot is mounted with a hinged cover complete with two gold chains. The mounts are Netherlandish, circa 1720, and the teapot is from the Kangxi period (1662-1722).</p>\r\r\n', '', '1950', 'GBP', 'GBP', 'Shelf 10', 'AAA', '<p>Exh. Cat. Couven-Museum Aachen, 2003, no. 84 For a Yixing teapot with contemporary gold mounts, circa 1700, the mounts with 1908-1953 Dutch import marks, see Sotheby&rsquo;s, London, 4 June 2008, lot 210.</p>\r\r\n', '<p>DUTCH GOLDSMITH GOLD-MOUNTED CHINESE PORCELAIN TEAPOT spout mount with hinged cover, complete with two gold chains 10cm, 4in high The mounts Netherlandish, circa 1720, the teapot Kangxi period (1662&ndash;1722)</p>\r\r\n', 'Active', '', '0', '', '', '', '', 'Yes'),
(463, '<p>George II Silver Lemon Strainer</p>\r\r\n', '1355724000', '0000-00-00', '1729', '16.5', '0', '0', '3', '500', 0, 'No', '410', '<p>Shaped lug handles, one engraved with initials F over I*I. A lemon strainer was used when making punch. This silver example dates from 1827 and was made by D. C. Rait of Glasgow. Lemons were cut and squeezed over the perforations, letting the juic', '<p>London no makers mark</p>\r\r\n', '150', 'GBP', 'GBP', 'Shelf 9', 'D', '', '<p>George II Silver Lemon Strainer</p>\r\r\n', 'Active', '', '0', '', '', '', '', 'Yes'),
(464, '<p>English Indian Style Tea Set</p>\r\r\n', '1358402400', '0000-00-00', '1879 (tea Set) 1887 (tongs)', '16', '13', '0', '23', '2000', 0, 'No', '411', '<p>A highly unusual English tea set done in a wonderful chased design of interweaving floral style that runs from the plain base stand up to a simple plain banding around the rim and continues on to the tip of the finial. The work is in Indian style,', '<p>Hunt &amp; Roskell (clockmaker/watchmaker; merchant/financier; British; Male; 1843 - c.1965) Address 156 New Bond Street, London W 26 Harrison St, nr Clerkenwell Biography Silversmiths and jewellers to Queen Victoria. Successors to Mortimer &amp; ', '0', 'GBP', 'GBP', 'Shelf 15', 'B', '', '<p>AN UNUSUAL THREE PEICE VICTORIAN TEA SET BY HUNT AND ROSKELL, LONDON 1879</p>\r\r\n', 'Active', '', '0', '', '', '', '', 'Yes'),
(465, '<p>The Millennium Comission Silver Teapot</p>\r\r\n', '1358316000', '0000-00-00', '2000', '24', '20', '0', '0', '3000', 0, 'No', '412', '<p>This simple and elegant teapot was designed as a Millennium Comission for exhibition at the Fitzwilliam Museum, Cambridge. Three were made in total, and the other two also reside in private collections. The dark ebony colored wood complements the ', '<p>Tara Coomber completed a National Diploma in General Art &amp; Design at the Kent Institute of General Art &amp; Design. She then went on to study her BA (Hons) in Jewellery and Silversmithing at the Birmingham School of Jewellery, graduating in 1', '0', 'GBP', 'GBP', 'Shelf 15', 'B', '', '<p>A RARE AND UNUSUAL SILVER TEAPOT BY TARA M COOMBER 2000</p>\r\r\n', 'Active', '', '0', '', '', '', '', 'Yes'),
(466, '<p>Three Piece Chinese Export Tea Set</p>\r\r\n', '1354600800', '0000-00-00', '19th century', '0', '15.5', '0', '30', '2000', 0, 'No', '413', '<p>Marked with character mark to base, comprising a teapot, covered twin handled sugar bowl and milk jug, each of square section with planished finials and a circular cartouche inscribed with characters, the handles naturalistically formed as bamboo.', '', '600', 'GBP', 'GBP', 'Shelf 15', 'C', '', '<p>Three Piece Chinese Export Silver Tea Set teapot 15.5cm high, combined weight 30oz</p>\r\r\n', 'Active', '', '0', '', '', '', '', 'Yes'),
(467, '<p>Pair of Chinese Yellow Ground Tea Bowls</p>\r\r\n', '1354600800', '0000-00-00', '19th century', '8', '5.5', '0', '0', '420', 0, 'No', '414', '<p>Two deep bowls with a plain interior, the exteriors decorated with an allover white blossom pattern, red four character Tongzhi mark.</p>\r\r\n', '', '126', 'GBP', 'GBP', 'Shelf 2', 'B', '', '<p>Pair of Chinese Yellow Ground Tea Bowls QING DYNASTY, 19TH CENTURY 8cm diam, 505cm high</p>\r\r\n', 'Active', '', '0', '', '', '', '', 'Yes'),
(468, '<p>3 Piece Silver Tea Set in Purple Box</p>\r\r\n', '1358402400', '0000-00-00', '1896', '0', '0', '0', '0', '1100', 0, 'No', '415', '<p>A stunning three piece tea set with dark ebony wooden handles with clean silver centre&#39;s chased with floral furn motives don both sides. the set has a wonderful set of tongs all of which is contained within a dark leather case with a vibrant p', '<p>Sheffield SF over WS into a shield (Fenton Bros (Samuel Fenton &amp; William Staniforth [ L ] ) 19th c./2nd half</p>\r\r\n', '0', 'GBP', 'GBP', 'Shelf 17', 'C', '', '<p>3 Piece Sterling Silver Tea Set in Purple Box made in 1896 Sheffield</p>\r\r\n', 'Active', '', '0', '', '', '', '', 'Yes'),
(469, '<p>Three Piece tea set with doves</p>\r\r\n', '1358402400', '0000-00-00', '1874', '0', '0', '0', '0', '3200', 0, 'No', '416', '<p>A stunningly worked three piece tea set with engraved plants and doves which are juxtaposed with silver gilt worked flowering vines and a silver gilt Finial of a rose. The floral theme continues to both the spout and the handle which has ivory ins', '<p>Goldsmiths Alliance Ltd -Samuel Smily-, Samuel Smily was manager of A.B. Savory &amp; Sons silver manufactory, suceeding his father William Smily. He retired in 1880 London 1871.</p>\r\r\n', '0', 'GBP', 'GBP', 'Shelf 16', 'B', '', '<p>Three Piece tea set London 1874 Samuel Smily</p>\r\r\n', 'Active', '', '0', '', '', '', '', 'No');
