(470, '<p>Five Piece Tea Set in Wooden Case</p>\r\r\n', '1358661600', '0000-00-00', '1868', '0', '0', '0', '0', '13000', 0, 'No', '417', '<p>This amazing five piece set has two matching trays and the original wooden storage box. A classical Greek motif runs through out the entire set reflecting the Victorians&#39; love affair with ancient Greek culture and the burgeoning interest in ar', '<p>Samuel Roberts and Charles Belk for Roberts and Belk. hallmark entered in London on June 2, 1865. The firm was established as Furniss, Poles &amp; Turner. The first hallmark was entered in Sheffield Assay Office as &quot;plate worker, Furnival Str', '0', 'GBP', 'GBP', 'Shelf 3', 'A', '', '<p>A VICTORIAN STERLING SILVER FIVE PEICE TEASET AND TWO TRAYS BY ROBERTS AND BELKS SHEFFIELD 1868</p>\r\r\n', 'Active', '', '0', '', '', '', '', 'No'),
(471, '<p>The Blue Cockerel Teapot</p>\r\r\n', '1358661600', '0000-00-00', '1780', '0', '0', '0', '0', '3000', 0, 'No', '418', '<p>This unusual cobalt blue teapot has a highly unusual sunken niche containing a cockerel and eggs. A tiny silver gilt cockerel also appears on the spout cover. A floral design runs over the rest of the teapot.</p>\r\r\n', '', '0', 'GBP', 'GBP', 'Shelf 2', 'A', '', '<p>AN 18TH CENTURY JAPANESE SILVER MOUNTED PORCELIAN TEA KETTLE CIRCA 1780</p>\r\r\n', 'Active', '', '0', '', '', '', '', 'Yes'),
(472, '<p>Silver Mounted Imari Porcelain Teapot</p>\r\r\n', '1358661600', '0000-00-00', 'C 1740', '0', '0', '0', '0', '2000', 0, 'No', '419', '<p>An Imari porcelain teapot with later silver finial and rim mounts. a floral red and cobalt blue pattern runs through out the pot with a western zig-zaging pattern around the rim chased in gold.</p>\r\r\n', '<p>Although there are many types of Imaris, Westerners&#39; conception of Imari in popular sense has association with only a type of Imari produced and exported in large quantity in mid-17th century. The type is called Kinrande. Kinrande Imari is col', '0', 'GBP', 'GBP', 'Shelf 8', 'B', '', '<p>Silver Mounted Imari Porcelain Teapot CIRCA 1740</p>\r\r\n', 'Active', '', '0', '', '', '', '', 'Yes'),
(473, '<p>Blue and White Kraak Porcelain Silver Mounted Teapot</p>\r\r\n', '1355292000', '0000-00-00', '1573-1619', '0', '15.5', '0', '0', '800', 0, 'No', '420', '<p>The barrel-shaped body of this teapot is painted with vertical panels of peony, bamboo, chrysanthemum, prunus and birds. It has a short S-shaped spout and is mounted with a silver overhead handle and with a silver cover.</p>\r\r\n', '<p>Property of a Dutch noble family</p>\r\r\n', '242', 'EUR', 'EUR', 'Shelf 5', 'AAA', '', '<p>A Chinese Blue and White Kraak Porcelain Silver Mounted Teapot</p>\r\r\n', 'Active', '', '0', '', '', '', '', 'Yes'),
(474, '<p>Pair of Famille Rose Flower Encrusted Teapots</p>\r\r\n', '1355119200', '0000-00-00', '1736-1795 ', '0', '9.5', '0', '0', '1500', 0, 'No', '421', '<p>Each of globular shape, with C-shaped dragon-head handle and dragon-head spout, the sides and flat cover encrusted with flowering branches.</p>\r\r\n', '', '453.75', 'EUR', 'EUR', 'Shelf 4', 'B', '', '<p>A Pair of Chinese Famille Rose Flower Encrusted Teapots</p>\r\r\n', 'Active', '', '0', '', '', '', '', 'Yes'),
(475, '<p>Silver Tea Urn With Braided Detail</p>\r\r\n', '1358402400', '0000-00-00', '1776', '0', '53', '0', '163', '32000', 0, 'No', '423', '<p>The typical shape of a crater in the middle teapot decorated with festoons enclosing grounds in front of a coat of arms. At the bottom Ribbed, taken in the form of snakes entwined and molding shaped cone, nozzle spout terminating in the head of a ', '<p>Maker&rsquo;s mark of Nicholas Dumee, London William Holmes: free of the Lorimers&#39; Company (records destroyed 1940, but so described in later apprenticeships to him in Goldsmiths&#39; records). Apparently working by about 1762, since pieces be', '0', 'GBP', 'GBP', 'Shelf 2', 'A', '', '<p>GEORGE III Silver Tea Urn MADE LONDON 1776 BY NICHOLAS DUMEE</p>\r\r\n', 'Active', '', '0', '', '', '', '', 'Yes'),
(476, '<p>A Chinese Silver Export Urn with Snake Spout</p>\r\r\n', '1358402400', '0000-00-00', '1825', '17', '31.5', '19', '1640', '5000', 0, 'No', '424', '<p>This Chinese urn has a snake headed spout that coils itself around one foot of the urn and presents its head as the spigot terminal, bearing a classical ivory finial. The serpent appears in English Georgian silver, but usually as an integral detai', '<p>Canton, by Lin Chong Lin Chong of Canton was a master. The quality of workmanship rivaled that of Paul Storr, yet because of his geographical remoteness to the source of British Georgian silver, it is not uncommon to find a degree of artistic lice', '0', 'GBP', 'GBP', 'Shelf 15', 'A', '', '<p>A Chinese Silver Export Urn MADE CANTON CIRCA 1825 BY LIN CHONG</p>\r\r\n', 'Active', '', '0', '', '', '', '', 'Yes'),
(477, '<p>Chinese Umbrella Tea and Coffee Set</p>\r\r\n', '1358834400', '0000-00-00', '1825-1827', '0', '0', '0', '0', '5000', 0, 'No', '422', '<p>This stunning teaset depicts an English stereotype of the Orient, with various typical scenes of the far East on the sides. The finials depict Chinese men holding traditional paper umbrellas.</p>\r\r\n', '<p>Jonathan Hayne London 1827 (coffee pot 1825). Jonathan Hayne was apprenticed to Thomas Wallis II on 1st January 1796. He became free on 4th June 1804 and registered his mark on 14th November 1808, as a large-worker. This was only a very short peri', '0', 'GBP', 'GBP', 'Shelf 9', 'B', '', '<p>A GEORGE FOUR TEA AND COFFEE SET BY JONATHAN HAYNE LONDON 1827 (THE COFFEE POT 1825)</p>\r\r\n', 'Active', '', '0', '', '', '', '', 'Yes'),
(478, '<p>Silver and Blue Enamel Tea Caddy</p>\r\r\n', '1357797600', '0000-00-00', '1877-1891', '0', '12.2', '0', '9', '18000', 0, 'No', '425', '<p>This tea caddy is of globular form, the hammered surfaced chased with vari-colored strands of enamel beads in blue, green, red and yellow. The shoulder is chased with a spiral border and the cover with conforming spiral and enamel beading has a bl', '<p>Property of a Mississippi Collector. A Tiffany jug with similar enameled beaded decoration sold in these Rooms, 18-19 January 2002, lot 253. also marked 4824/5305/2285.</p>\r\r\n', '4500', 'USD', 'USD', 'Shelf 2', 'A', '', '<p>A SILVER AND ENAMEL TEA CADDY<br />\r\r\nMARK OF TIFFANY &amp; CO., NEW YORK, 1877-1891<br />\r\r\nGlobular, the hammered surfaced chased with vari-colored strands of enamel beads in blue, green, red and yellow, the shoulder chased with spiral border, t', 'Active', '', '0', '', '', '', '<p>Date changed as per Mr Sethia&#39;s instructions on 28/10/13.</p>\r\r\n\r\r\n<p>Chloe notes: however Tiffany&#39;s wasn&#39;t yet founded in the dates Mr Sethia changed it to.&nbsp; The company was founded in 1837.</p>\r\r\n', 'Yes'),
(479, '<p>Silver Mixed-Metal and Hardstone Three-piece Tea Service</p>\r\r\n', '1357797600', '0000-00-00', 'C 1880', '18.8', '0', '0', '37', '100000', 0, 'No', '426', '<p>This tea set, comprising a teapot, covered sugar bowl, cream jug, and sugar tongs, was one of Tiffany &amp; Co.&#39;s most successful creations. Designed in the Japanesque style by Tiffany&#39;s director, Edward C. Moore, the tea set contributed t', '<p>Frances Lent, New York City, 1880. A teapot and another teapot and cream jug of this pattern sold in these Rooms, respectively, 19 January 2012, lot 55 and 18-19 January 2002, lots 258-259. Another three-piece service sold Sotheby&#39;s, New York,', '22500', 'USD', 'USD', 'Shelf 8', 'AAA', '<p>A similar teapot, with a matte (but not hammered) finish, is in the collection of the New-York Historical Society and illustrated in John Loring, Magnificent Tiffany Silver, 2001, p. 59. Another teapot and sugar bowl of the same form of this and t', '<p>AN AMERICAN SILVER AND MIXED METAL THREE PEICE TEA SERVICE WITH TONGS, TIFFANY AND CO</p>\r\r\n', 'Active', '', '0', '', '', '', '', 'Yes'),
