(481, '<p>Staffordshire Salt-Glazed Polychrome-Enamled Teapot and Stand</p>\r\r\n', '1360476000', '0000-00-00', 'C 1760', '19', '0', '0', '0', '5000', 0, 'No', '428', '<p>The teapot with crabstock handle and spout, enameled in the Chinese taste with a colorful bird perched on rockwork among flowering vine; the shaped-square tray press-molded and enameled with radiating flower-heads and foliage.</p>\r\r\n', '<p>With Guitel Montague, New York 1 February 1936 (paper label, the teapot). W.B. Goodwin, collection nos. 53 and 67. Exhibited Portland Museum of Art, loan nos. 2.1983.58 and .6.</p>\r\r\n', '1250', 'USD', 'USD', 'Shelf 4', 'B', '<p>See Arnold R. Mountford, The Illustrated Guide to Staffordshire Saltglaze Stoneware, London, 1971, fig. 179 for a similar teapot. For a corresponding sweatmeat tray block of hardened copper and a related undecorated saltglazed stoneware example, s', '<p>Staffordshire Salt-Glazed Polychrome-Enamled Teapot and Stand circa 1760</p>\r\r\n', 'Active', '', '0', '', '', '', '', 'Yes'),
