(640, '<p>Engraved Teapot</p>\r\r\n', '1366693200', '0000-00-00', 'C 1854', '0', '0', '0', '0', '80', 0, 'No', 'A81', '<p>Rococo inspired embossed bullet teapot sat on a ribbed pedestal.</p>\r\r\n', '', '0', 'GBP', 'GBP', 'None Assigned', 'Q', '<p>The origin of the firm is in the partnership established in 1820 in Sheffield by Henry Wilkinson and John Roberts who traded as Wilkinson &amp; Roberts. Wilkinson left the business in 1836 and in 1846 John Roberts entered in partnership with Ebene', '', 'Inactive', 'Sold', '88', 'GBP', 'Newby Singapore', '', '', 'No'),
(641, '<p>Samovar of water drop shape</p>\r\r\n', '1398229200', '0000-00-00', '1875', '0', '0', '0', '0', '320', 0, 'No', 'A82', '<p>A droplet shaped samovar with a elongated lid and art-deco style handles. This tea urn has lightly engraved work around the body and base.</p>\r\r\n', '', '0', 'GBP', 'GBP', 'None Assigned', 'Q', '<p>The business established itself in Sheffield in 1845 and in 1853 changed the name to Walker &amp; Hall. They had branches across various cities in the UK, and in Australia, and South Africa.</p>\r\r\n', '', 'Inactive', 'Sold', '352', 'GBP', 'Newby Singapore', '', '', 'No'),
(642, '<p>Zodiac Teapot</p>\r\r\n', '1366693200', '0000-00-00', 'C- 1903', '0', '0', '0', '0', '70', 0, 'No', 'A83', '<p>This teapot is heavy in embossed detailing with zodiac signs and foliage around the body.</p>\r\r\n', '', '0', 'GBP', 'GBP', 'None Assigned', 'Q', '<p>Thomas Ross &amp; Sons, established 1901 in Glasgow</p>\r\r\n', '', 'Inactive', 'Sold', '77', 'GBP', 'Newby Singapore', '', '', 'No'),
(643, '<p>Scroll work engraved 3 Piece Tea set</p>\r\r\n', '1366693200', '0000-00-00', '1863-1910', '0', '0', '0', '0', '120', 0, 'No', 'A84', '<p>A three-piece can shapped tea set with engraved scroll work.</p>\r\r\n', '', '0', 'GBP', 'GBP', 'None Assigned', 'Q', '<p>Alfred and Frederick Briddon founded Briddon Brothers in 1863. The bcame Briddon Brothers &amp; Co. Ltd. in 1905 until 1910.</p>\r\r\n', '', 'Inactive', 'Sold', '132', 'GBP', 'Newby Singapore', '', '', 'No'),
(644, '<p>Teapot with Bud finial</p>\r\r\n', '1366693200', '0000-00-00', '1867', '0', '0', '0', '0', '80', 0, 'No', 'A85', '<p>Pear-shaped teapot with engraved detailing and a bud finial. The spout is heavily embossed.</p>\r\r\n', '', '0', 'GBP', 'GBP', 'None Assigned', 'Q', '', '', 'Inactive', 'Sold', '88', 'GBP', 'Newby Singapore', '', '', 'No'),
(645, '<p>Teapot With Scale Pattern</p>\r\r\n', '1366693200', '0000-00-00', '1874', '0', '0', '0', '0', '80', 0, 'No', 'A86', '<p>A teapot with embossed floral detailing and a scale-like pattern around the neck.</p>\r\r\n', '', '0', 'GBP', 'GBP', 'None Assigned', 'Q', '<p>William &amp; George Sissons entered their first hallmark in 1864. They were based in Sheffield. In 1887 Walter and Charles Sissons took over.</p>\r\r\n', '', 'Inactive', 'Sold', '88', 'GBP', 'Newby Singapore', '', '', 'No'),
(646, '<p>Flower finial teapot</p>\r\r\n', '1366693200', '0000-00-00', '1863', '0', '0', '0', '0', '80', 0, 'No', 'A89', '<p>A teapot with embossed decoration around the body, and a plain lid with a flower-like finial.</p>\r\r\n', '', '0', 'GBP', 'GBP', 'None Assigned', 'Q', '<p>Roberts &amp; Belk became partners of an already established silversmiths in Sheffield, in 1863. In 1879 Roberts retired but Belk continued to produce items in the Roberts &amp; Belk style. In 1901 the business became known as Roberts &amp; Belk L', '', 'Inactive', 'Sold', '88', 'GBP', 'Newby Singapore', '', '', 'No'),
(647, '<p>Pedestal Teapot</p>\r\r\n', '1366693200', '0000-00-00', '1853', '0', '0', '0', '0', '80', 0, 'No', 'A90', '<p>A pedestal teapot with embossed Grecian patterning. The handle creates a juxtaposition in styles dues to its angularity.</p>\r\r\n', '', '0', 'GBP', 'GBP', 'None Assigned', 'Q', '<p>James Dixon and Sons established themselves in 1806 in Sheffield. They were a very successful manufacturing company during the industrial revolution. The business continued through the family line until 1976.</p>\r\r\n', '', 'Inactive', 'Sold', '88', 'GBP', 'Newby Singapore', '', '', 'No'),
(648, '<p>3 Piece Tea set</p>\r\r\n', '1366693200', '0000-00-00', '1853', '0', '0', '0', '0', '80', 0, 'No', 'A91', '<p>This three-piece tea set (teapot, creamer, and sugar bowl) is simply designed with fine lines engraved down the body of each item. The teapot&#39;s finial complements the simplicity of the set with a round head.</p>\r\r\n', '', '0', 'GBP', 'GBP', 'None Assigned', 'Q', '<p>In 1831 Willaim Watson retired from partnership with Thomas Bradbury. The business carried on under the new name Thomas Bradbury &amp; Son until 1855 when the two sons of Thomas Bradbury II took over; the firm was then called Thomas Bradbury &amp;', '', 'Inactive', 'Sold', '88', 'GBP', 'Newby Singapore', '', '', 'No'),
(649, '<p>Mirror Tea Kettle</p>\r\r\n', '1366693200', '0000-00-00', '1852', '0', '0', '0', '0', '240', 0, 'No', 'A92', '<p>This kettle has a plain rounded body with a heavy handle and floral finial. The silversmith has used a pierced technique on the stand.</p>\r\r\n', '', '0', 'GBP', 'GBP', 'None Assigned', 'Q', '<p>Thomas and James Creswick started business in 1815 under the name T &amp; J Creswick. In 1819 Nathaniel Creswick joined forming T. J. &amp; N Creswick. They began eletroplating in 1852.</p>\r\r\n', '', 'Inactive', 'Sold', '264', 'GBP', 'Newby Singapore', '', '', 'No'),
(650, '<p>Victorian Silver Seven Piece Tea and Coffee Set</p>\r\r\n', '1366002000', '0000-00-00', '1874', '0', '0', '0', '0', '14000', 0, 'No', '519', '<p>This tea set comprises a teapot, coffee pot, kettle on lampstand, hot milk pot, creamer, smaller creamer, and open sugar bowl, of compressed circular and baluster form. All are chased with finely detailed bands of Indian style foliage and each wit', '<p>Fully marked and signed GOLDSMITHS ALLIANCE LIMITED CORNHILL LONDON, the kettle also with design registry mark.</p>\r\r\n', '3500', 'USD', 'USD', 'Shelf 16', 'A', '<p>See John Culme in The Directory of Gold and Silversmiths, Jewellers and Allied traders 1838-1914, who notes Samuel Smily&#39;s registration with the patent office in 1876 for an &quot;Indian pattern tea kettle with Chinese dragon handles.&quot;</p', '<p>Victorian Silver Indian style Seven Piece Tea and Coffee Set, Samuel Smily, London, 1874</p>\r\r\n', 'Active', '', '0', '', '', '', '', 'Yes'),
(651, '<p>Queen Anne Urn</p>\r\r\n', '1367470800', '0000-00-00', '1702', '0', '0', '0', '0', '21000', 0, 'No', '520', '<p>This extremely rare urn by Francis Singleton is made from Britannia Standard silver with applied cut-card work and three tall scroll feet. Very few of these small urns are extant in English silver and this example may well be the earliest hallmark', '', '0', 'GBP', 'GBP', 'Shelf 14', 'AAA', '<p>Michael Clayton, in the Collectors Dictionary of Silver and Gold of Great Britain and North America, pages 424-426 illustrates and describes a small urn by Thomas Bolton, Dublin, 1696. Although there survives an urn with spigot tap made by Thomas ', '<p>Queen Anne urn London 1702, Francis Singleton</p>\r\r\n', 'Active', '', '0', '', '', '', '', 'Yes'),
(652, '<p>Ivory Finial Caddy</p>\r\r\n', '1367470800', '0000-00-00', '1875', '0', '0', '0', '0', '225', 0, 'No', 'A93', '<p>An oval tea caddy with engraved floral garlands around the body. There is an engraved pattern on the lid similar to the carved ivory finial.</p>\r\r\n', '', '0', 'GBP', 'GBP', 'None Assigned', 'Q', '', '', 'Inactive', 'Sold', '247.5', 'GBP', 'Newby Singapore', '', '', 'No'),
(653, '<p>Shield Tea Kettle</p>\r\r\n', '1367470800', '0000-00-00', '1870', '0', '52', '0', '0', '450', 0, 'No', 'A94', '<p>A Victorian tea kettle shaped in a manner evoking a shield. The finial similar to a trophy. The body of the kettle is delicately engraved with recurring patterns. The legs of the&nbsp; stand represent a goats head and its leg and the corners of th', '', '0', 'GBP', 'GBP', 'None Assigned', 'Q', '<p>Elkington and Co. established themselves in Birmingham during the 1830s. Between 1842 and 1861 the name was changed to Elkington, Mason, &amp; Co. due to the addition of a third partner; but then returned back to Elkington and Co. until 1863 when ', '', 'Inactive', 'Sold', '495', 'GBP', 'Newby Singapore', '', '', 'No'),
(654, '<p>Chinoiserie Caddy</p>\r\r\n', '1367470800', '0000-00-00', '1860', '0', '15', '0', '0', '225', 0, 'No', 'A95', '<p>A chinoiserie tea caddy with embossed detailing representing a woman collecting plants in a basket. There is also a lion&#39;s head discernable above the woman. The finial of this caddy is in the shape of the tree stump.</p>\r\r\n', '', '0', 'GBP', 'GBP', 'None Assigned', 'Q', '', '', 'Inactive', 'Sold', '247.5', 'GBP', 'Newby Singapore', '', '', 'No'),
(655, '<p>Afternoon Tea set with Tray</p>\r\r\n', '1365656400', '0000-00-00', '1890', '0', '0', '0', '0', '750', 0, 'No', 'A65', '<p>A spectacular tea set on a enormous tray. This set is dominated by the tea kettle on a burner that rises above the teapot and other accruements.</p>\r\r\n', '', '0', 'GBP', 'GBP', 'None Assigned', 'Q', '<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\r\n\r\r\n<p><strong>The firm was established in 1865 by James Deakin at Sidney Works, Matilda Street, Sheffield. Before 1886 he was joined in partnership by his three sons, William Pitchford, John and Albert and the style of the firm was ch', '', 'Inactive', 'Sold', '825', 'GBP', 'Newby Singapore', '', '', 'No'),
(656, '<p>Picnic Tea Set with Tray</p>\r\r\n', '1365656400', '0000-00-00', 'Circa 1880', '0', '0', '0', '0', '200', 0, 'No', 'A66', '<p>A clean flowing style tea set resting on a waving tea tray that compliments the style of the tea set. The light brown of the wooden handles keeps to the clean elegant style of the tea and coffe pots body.</p>\r\r\n', '', '0', 'GBP', 'GBP', 'None Assigned', 'Q', '<h3><em>MARKS - HALLMARKS - HISTORY</em></h3>\r\r\n\r\r\n<p>The business was founded in London by Robert Pringle (I) in 1835.<br />\r\r\nThe activity was continued by his son, Robert Pringle (II). In c.1882 the firm was changed to Robert Pringle &amp; Co.<br ', '', 'Inactive', 'Sold', '220', 'GBP', 'Newby Singapore', '', '', 'No'),
(657, '<p>Ivory Handled tea set.</p>\r\r\n', '1365656400', '0000-00-00', 'Circa 1840', '0', '0', '0', '0', '1650', 0, 'No', 'A67', '<p>A hyper decorated tea set with almost every inch covered in ornate designs. This is contrasted by the X shaped kettle stand that holds the center peice kettle.</p>\r\r\n', '', '0', 'GBP', 'GBP', 'None Assigned', 'Q', '', '', 'Inactive', 'Sold', '1815', 'GBP', 'Newby Singapore', '', '', 'No'),
(658, '<p>Mirrored Vase Tea Pot</p>\r\r\n', '1365656400', '0000-00-00', '1875', '0', '0', '0', '0', '75', 0, 'No', 'A69', '', '<p>A mirrored vase tea pot with an elaborate spout and handle contrasting the smooth body. The tea pot is raised on a pedestal base with a raise finial made from bone.</p>\r\r\n', '0', 'GBP', 'GBP', 'None Assigned', 'Q', '<h3>The origin of the firm is in the partnership established in 1820 in Sheffield by Henry Wilkinson and John Roberts who traded as Wilkinson &amp; Roberts. Wilkinson left the business in 1836 and in 1846 John Roberts entered in partnership with Eben', '', 'Inactive', 'Sold', '82.5', 'GBP', 'Newby Singapore', '', '', 'No'),
(659, '<p>Barrel Teapot</p>\r\r\n', '1365656400', '0000-00-00', '1875', '0', '0', '0', '0', '75', 0, 'No', 'A70', '<p>A corrugated teapot with an overall barrel shape. A mirror handle and spout contrast the corrugated body.</p>\r\r\n', '', '0', 'GBP', 'GBP', 'None Assigned', 'Q', '', '', 'Inactive', 'Sold', '82.5', 'GBP', 'Newby Singapore', '', '', 'No'),
(660, '<p>Ebony Black Handle Tea and Coffee Set</p>\r\r\n', '1365656400', '0000-00-00', '1890', '0', '0', '0', '0', '850', 0, 'No', 'A71', '<p>A tea and coffee set of delicate design, with fine engraving work. this set is dominated by the dark ebony wood of the handles and finials of the kettle, teapot and coffee pot.</p>\r\r\n', '', '0', 'GBP', 'GBP', 'None Assigned', 'Q', '<p><a name="POT11">John Henry Potter, 124 Rockingam St., 1884-1893. Rockingam Works, 65-71 Division St. 1893-1940. The firm became J.P. Potter &amp; Sons Ltd in 1922. The firm used the trade marks SILVA and ROCKINGHAM PLATE</a></p>\r\r\n', '', 'Inactive', 'Sold', '935', 'GBP', 'Newby Singapore', '', '', 'No'),
(661, '<p>Dresden Silver-Gilt Mounted Rubinglas Ewer</p>\r\r\n', '1367384400', '0000-00-00', 'glass 1713-18; mounts c 1750', '0', '0', '0', '0', '15000', 0, 'No', '521', '<p>This ewer was designed in honour of Augustus the Strong, Elector of Saxony and King of Poland, whose royal arms appear on the pot. The glass, created between 1713 and 1718, was produced by Johann B&ouml;ttger, an alchemist and craftsman at the ear', '<p>Provenance: Anon. sale, Sotheby&#39;s, 10 February 1986, lot 178 Dresden, circa 1713-18, the mounts circa 1750. The compressed globular form with short cylindrical neck and applied S-shaped spout, decorated on one side with the cypher AR within ti', '4500', 'GBP', 'GBP', 'Shelf 3', 'AAA', '<p>Dedo von Kerssenbrock-Krosigk, Rubinglas des ausgehenden 17. und des 18. Jahrhunderts (2001), p.224, no.282 For two identical examples: in the Germanisches Nationalmuseum, Nuremberg and in a private collection respectively, see von Kerssenbrock-Kr', '<p>A rare Dresden engraved silver gilt mounted armorial rubinglas teapot, Dresden C1713-18, the mounts C1750</p>\r\r\n', 'Active', '', '0', '', '', '', '', 'Yes'),
(662, '<p>Willow and Ivory Tea set</p>\r\r\n', '1365656400', '0000-00-00', '1880', '0', '0', '0', '0', '400', 0, 'No', 'A72', '<p>A light almost modern tea set resting on a mirror tray with ivory colored willow wood handles. The unusual finials on the coffee and tea pot which depicts a sculpted man in repose possibly meditation fit with the oriental theme of the engravings o', '', '0', 'GBP', 'GBP', 'None Assigned', 'Q', '<p>The firm, active as manufacturing silversmiths and electroplaters, was established in Birmingham in 1855. In 1875 the firm entered its mark in Birmingham Assay Office, while in 1879 the founders Jonathan Wilson Hukin and John Thomas Heath entered ', '', 'Inactive', 'Sold', '440', 'GBP', 'Newby Singapore', '', '', 'No'),
(663, '<p>Austrian Silver-Gilt, Enamel, Rock Crystal, and Gem Set Spoon</p>\r\r\n', '1367989200', '0000-00-00', '1880', '0', '0', '0', '0', '650', 0, 'No', '522', '<p>This rock crystal spoon is Viennese, and was designed in the Renaissance style.</p>\r\r\n', '<p>Came in a lot with a French Rococo style silver-mounted rock crystal dish by Eugene Michel, late 19th century, of lozenge form, the bottom etched with the figure of Mercury and inscribed &#39;E. Michel.&#39;</p>\r\r\n', '162', 'USD', 'USD', 'Shelf 8', 'S', '', '<p>An Austrian Silver-Gilt, Enamel, Rock Crystal, and Gem Set Spoon by Herman Ratzerdorfer, Vienna C1880</p>\r\r\n', 'Active', '', '0', '', '', '', '', 'Yes'),
(664, '<p>Lavender-Ground Vienna Tea Set</p>\r\r\n', '1367989200', '0000-00-00', '19th century', '0', '0', '0', '0', '16000', 0, 'No', '523', '<p>This ten piece tete-a-tete tea set is finely painted with mythological panels centered by elaborate borders of Neoclassical reserves within gilt borders. The set includes a rectangular tray, coffee pot, two coffee cans with saucers and covers, a s', '', '4000', 'USD', 'USD', 'Shelf 3', 'AAA', '', '<p>A Vienna style porcelain lavender-ground ten piece tete-a-tete 19th century, including covers</p>\r\r\n', 'Active', '', '0', '', '', '', '', 'Yes'),
