(790, '<p>Twelve Niello Teaspoons</p>\r\r\n', '1371099600', '0000-00-00', 'C 1889', '0', '0', '0', '0', '3100', 0, 'No', '633', '<p>A set of 12 silver gilt niello teaspoons, maker&#39;s mark &quot;2MA&quot;, Moscow, circa 1889. The reverse of the each bowl decorated with an architectural view, traditional twist handle that terminates into a knop finial, contained in a fitted b', '', '0', 'USD', 'USD', 'Shelf 5', 'A', '', '<p>A set of 12 silver gilt niello teaspoons, maker&#39;s mark &quot;2MA&quot;, Moscow, circa 1889. The reverse of the each bowl decorated with an architectural view, traditional twist handle that terminates into a knop finial, contained in a fitted b', 'Active', '', '0', '', '', '', '', 'Yes'),
(791, '<p>Twelve Faberge Enamel Teaspoon</p>\r\r\n', '1371099600', '0000-00-00', '1908-1917', '0', '0', '0', '0', '27500', 0, 'No', '634', '<p>A set of twelve Faberge silver-gilt and shaded cloisonne enamel teaspoons, workmaster Feodor Ruckert, Moscow, circa 1908-1917, scratched inventory number 25218. The reverse of each bowl is enameled with Pan-Slavic style shaded polychrome stylized ', '', '0', 'USD', 'USD', 'Shelf 5', 'A', '', '<p>A set of twelve Faberge silver-gilt and shaded cloisonne enamel teaspoons, workmaster Feodor Ruckert, Moscow, circa 1908-1917, scratched inventory number 25218. The reverse of each bowl is enameled with Pan-Slavic style shaded polychrome stylized ', 'Active', '', '0', '', '', '', '', 'Yes'),
(794, '<p>Meissen Cafe au Lait Teapot</p>\r\r\n', '1372568400', '0000-00-00', 'C 1775', '0', '0', '0', '0', '4000', 0, 'No', '635', '<p>A Meissen cafe au lait coloured teapot with contemporary gilt metal mounts, painted with green flowers, c. 1775.</p>\r\r\n', '', '0', 'GBP', 'GBP', 'Shelf 5', 'A', '<p>R. Rukert Meissen Porzellan no 449, p109/112 Collection Fur Museum Kunst und Gerwerbe, Hamburg Inv. 1898</p>\r\r\n', '<p>A Meissen cafe au lait coloured teapot with contemporary gilt metal mounts, painted with green flowers, c. 1775. Literature: R. Rukert Meissen Porzellan no 449, p109/112 Collection For Museum Kunst und Gerwerbe, Hamburg Inv. 1898</p>\r\r\n', 'Active', '', '0', '', '', '', '', 'Yes'),
(795, '<p>Vienna Cup and Saucer with Silvered Ground</p>\r\r\n', '1372568400', '0000-00-00', '1793', '0', '0', '0', '0', '1500', 0, 'No', '636', '<p>Vienna Sorgenthal period cup and saucer with rare silvered ground and applied gold arabesques, from 1793. There is an incised mark 39 for the turner Ferdinand Ebenberuer (1793-1804).</p>\r\r\n', '', '0', 'GBP', 'GBP', 'Shelf 11', 'B', '', '<p>Vienna Sorgenthal period cup and saucer with rare silvered ground and applied gold arabesques, 1793. Incised mark 39 for the turner Ferdinand Ebenberuer (1793-1804).</p>\r\r\n', 'Active', '', '0', '', '', '', '', 'Yes'),
(796, '<p>First Period Worcester Teapot</p>\r\r\n', '1372568400', '0000-00-00', 'C 1775', '0', '0', '0', '0', '2700', 0, 'No', '637', '<p>A fine first period Worscter teapot, cover, and stand, decorated with a &quot;Mignonette&quot; border of puce garlands suspended between bright green panels above a &quot;fancy&quot; bird in foliate landscape, c. 1775.</p>\r\r\n', '', '0', 'GBP', 'GBP', 'Shelf 3', 'B', '', '<p>A fine first period Worscter teapot, cover, and stand, decorated with a &quot;Mignonette&quot; border of puce garlands suspended between bright green panels above a &quot;fancy&quot; bird in foliate landscape, c. 1775 (Tiny nibbles to flower finia', 'Active', '', '0', '', '', '', '', 'Yes'),
(797, '<p>Chelsea Derby Teacup and Saucer</p>\r\r\n', '1372568400', '0000-00-00', 'C 1775', '0', '0', '0', '0', '1500', 0, 'No', '638', '<p>A Chelsea Derby teacup and saucer, the claret ground with oeil-de-redrix decoration and classical busts/cameos with gilt medallions linked with foliate swags, c. 1775.</p>\r\r\n', '', '0', 'GBP', 'GBP', 'Shelf 11', 'C', '', '<p>A Chelsea Derby teacup and saucer, the claret ground with oeil-de-redrix decoration and classical busts/cameos with gilt medallions linked with foliate swags, c. 1775.</p>\r\r\n', 'Active', '', '0', '', '', '', '', 'Yes'),
(798, '<p>Ottoman Style Tea and Coffee Set</p>\r\r\n', '1372222800', '0000-00-00', 'C 1860', '0', '0', '0', '0', '38000', 0, 'No', '639', '<p>This rare French parcel-gilt silver tea and coffee service is in the Ottoman style by Henri Duponchel, Paris circa 1860, and is engraved with Cambac&eacute;r&egrave;s coat-of-arms. The set comprises a kettle on stand, coffee-pot, teapot, cream jug', '<p>Ad&egrave;le Davout d&#39;Auerstaedt d&#39;Eckm&uuml;hl (1807-1885), daughter of Marshal Davout, Prince Eckm&uuml;hl, who in 1827 married Count Stephen Cambac&eacute;r&egrave;s, son of Jean-Pierre Hubert Cambac&eacute;r&egrave;s brother Jean-Jacqu', '10883.6', 'EUR', 'EUR', 'Shelf 6', 'A', '<p>Henri Duponchel was born in Paris in 1794. He was a goldsmith, director, architect and designer. His earliest known work is as the developer of James and Salomon de Rothschild&#39;s hotels and in Paris. From 1835 to 1842 he was director of the Par', '<p>This rare French parcel-gilt silver tea and coffee service is in the Ottoman style by Henri Duponchel, Paris circa 1860</p>\r\r\n', 'Active', '', '0', '', '', '', '', 'Yes'),
(799, '<p>Italian Coffee Pot with a Greyhound Handle</p>\r\r\n', '1372222800', '0000-00-00', 'C 1820', '0', '0', '0', '0', '23000', 0, 'No', '640', '<p>This rare Italian silver large coffee-pot with a bronze handle in the shape of a greyhound is by Giovacchino Belli, Rome, circa 1820. The silver pot is set on four high paw feet topped by heads of lions, and rests on a circular wood loaded terrace', '', '6877', 'EUR', 'EUR', 'Shelf 14', 'A', '', '<p>This rare Italian silver large coffee-pot with a bronze handle in the shape of a greyhound is by Giovacchino Belli, Rome, circa 1820</p>\r\r\n', 'Active', '', '0', '', '', '', '', 'Yes'),
(800, '<p>French Silver Gilt Sugar Bowl</p>\r\r\n', '1372222800', '0000-00-00', '1780-1781', '0', '0', '0', '0', '10000', 0, 'No', '641', '<p>This large French silver-gilt sugar-bowl on stand is by Antoine Boullier, Paris, 1780-1781. The stand on four pilaster legs is surrounded by garlands, and decorated at the top with a beaded frieze. The body rests on four busts of women and an open', '<p>The arms are those of Jean-Florent Magnanville Robillard (1757-1834), Baron of the Empire from December 14, 1810, censor of the Bank of France from 1806 to 1824, who left at his death a fortune of more than two million francs.</p>\r\r\n', '2990', 'EUR', 'EUR', 'Shelf 15', 'A', '', '<p>This large French silver-gilt sugar-bowl on stand is by Antoine Boullier, Paris, 1780-1781.</p>\r\r\n', 'Active', '', '0', '', '', '', '', 'Yes'),
(801, '<p>George III Teapot on Stand</p>\r\r\n', '1372482000', '0000-00-00', '1812', '0', '0', '0', '0', '3750', 0, 'No', '642', '<p>A George III silver teapot on a stand, made in London 1812 by Paul Storr. Bearing the Arms for Maude who was the Viscount Howarden. The pot was possibly created for the Viscount&#39;s marriage, which took place in 1811 to Jane Crawford Bruce.</p>\r', '<p>Cornwallis Maude, 3rd Viscount Hawarden Cornwallis Maude, 3rd Viscount Hawarden (28 March 1780 &ndash; 12 October 1856) was a British Conservative politician. Hawarden was the son of Cornwallis Maude, 1st Viscount Hawarden, by his second wife Anne', '0', 'GBP', 'GBP', 'Shelf 5', 'A', '', '<p>A George III silver teapot on a stand, made in London 1812 by Paul Storr.</p>\r\r\n', 'Active', '', '0', '', '', '', '', 'Yes'),
(802, '<p>Chinese Mother of Pearl Box</p>\r\r\n', '1373000400', '0000-00-00', 'C 1770', '0', '0', '0', '0', '9000', 0, 'No', '643', '<p>A Chinese mother of pearl box.</p>\r\r\n', '', '0', 'GBP', 'GBP', 'Shelf 16', 'A', '', '<p>Chinese Mother of Pearl Box C1770</p>\r\r\n', 'Active', '', '0', '', '', '', '', 'Yes'),
(803, '<p>Miniature Tea Service</p>\r\r\n', '1370408400', '0000-00-00', '1768', '0', '0', '0', '0', '7800', 0, 'No', '644', '<p>A miniature tea service, &quot;dinnette,&quot; comprising a teapot, two cups and saucers, a covered sugarbowl and milk jug, very finely decorated with garlands of flowers on an &quot;oeil de perdrix&quot; ground Royal Manfactory of Sevres, circa 1', '', '0', 'GBP', 'GBP', 'Shelf 10', 'B', '', '<p>A miniature tea service, &quot;dinnette,&quot; comprising a teapot, two cups and saucers, a covered sugarbowl and milk jug, very finely decorated with garlands of flowers on an &quot;oeil de perdrix&quot; ground Royal Manufactory of Sevres, circa ', 'Active', '', '0', '', '', '', '', 'Yes');
